From: R9700 team <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: 2026-05-08
Subject: [PATCH] AWQConfig: extend bf16 act dtype support to HIP (R9700/RDNA4)

`AWQConfig.get_supported_act_dtypes` upstream v0.5.11 only allows bf16
activations on Ascend NPU (`_is_npu` carve-out at line 105).  R9700 ROCm
falls into the bare `AWQConfig` (no Marlin path on HIP), so loading a
Qwen3.5-arch AWQ model with bf16 weights is rejected:

  ValueError: torch.bfloat16 is not supported for quantization method awq.
              Supported dtypes: [torch.float16]

Forcing fp16 instead surfaces a downstream Triton kernel-compile crash
("Mismatched type for col0 between then block (bf16) and else block
(fp16)" in `triton_ops/decode_attention.py`) because the model's actual
weights are bf16 and the kernel's then-branch produces bf16 output.

3090 has patch 006 (`AWQMarlinConfig.get_supported_act_dtypes` returns
`[half, bfloat16]`) which v0.5.11 picked up upstream — but only for the
Marlin variant.  The bare non-Marlin `AWQConfig` was missed.  Same fix
shape, different class.

After patch: R9700 loads Qwen3-VL-32B-AWQ-balanced cleanly at TP=2 / 4K
with `dtype=bfloat16`; validate_capabilities 3/3 PASS in 20.3s, vision
content-aware ('a simple red circle with a black outline on a white
background').  Receipt at evals/awq-audit-2026-05-08-r9700-validate-receipt.md.

Discovered 2026-05-08 during R9700 hardware launch test (R9700 commit 9dc1ea5).

diff --git a/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/awq/awq.py b/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/awq/awq.py
--- a/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/awq/awq.py
+++ b/python/sglang/srt/layers/quantization/awq/awq.py
@@ -102,7 +102,15 @@ class AWQConfig(QuantizationConfig):
         return "awq"

     def get_supported_act_dtypes(self) -> List[torch.dtype]:
-        return [torch.float16] if not _is_npu else [torch.float16, torch.bfloat16]
+        # 2026-05-08 RDNA4 fix: extend bf16 support from NPU-only to also
+        # cover HIP (R9700/RDNA4 has no Marlin so falls into AWQConfig
+        # rather than AWQMarlinConfig; Qwen3.5-arch decode kernels expect
+        # bf16 throughout, fp16 dequant produces "Mismatched type for col0"
+        # Triton compilation crash). AWQ kernel supports bf16 act on HIP
+        # via the same Triton dispatch path AWQMarlinConfig uses on CUDA.
+        if _is_hip or _is_npu:
+            return [torch.float16, torch.bfloat16]
+        return [torch.float16]

     @classmethod
     def get_min_capability(cls) -> int:
